pulltitle: chore(worker): update linting to match activity stream main repo
pullsbody:
Fixes #31 
More than 300 lines of linting, plus file updates to catch up with AS.

I copied back from AS some files that were not changed since the beginning (e.g.: ActionManager.js, most of the content pages).

This is the first step to migrate the worker queue back to AS.
pull_repo_desc: UNMAINTAINED! An experimental addon that enriches the data about places in Firefox
pull_commit_message: chore(worker): update linting to match activity stream main repo

pulltitle: chore(worker): change Firefox version to the same on Activity Stream
pullsbody: It seems the `yield expression must be parenthesized` errors I was getting at version 46 were only happening when other errors happened. It hides the real error, so it makes debugging harder. I think it would be a good idea to update the AS Firefox version from time to time.

pulltitle: feat(workers): #5 a generic Task Processor to manage workers
pullsbody:
This PR implements a subclassable TaskProcessor and worker infrastructure.

The base TaskProcessor encapsulates the worker management responsabilities.
There is also an importable and extensible worker infrastructure.

Closes #5
